  <main class="doc" id="en">
    <div class="lead">
      touchABA is a behavior observation and functional assessment aid for <b>adult teachers and education professionals</b>.
      The current iPhone version is a <b>local-only app with no account sign-up, external server sync, advertising, analytics SDK, or voice input feature</b>.
      Observation records and assessment data are stored on the user's device by default and are not sent to the developer's server.
    </div>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">1.</span>Scope</h2>
      <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the touchABA app for iPhone distributed on the Apple App Store. The app is intended for adult users aged 18 or older, such as teachers, therapists, and education professionals. It is not directed to children.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">2.</span>Personal Information Collected by the Developer</h2>
      <p>The current version of touchABA does not use account registration, login, external server storage, advertising SDKs, or analytics SDKs. The developer does not collect or receive users' email addresses, names, passwords, location, contacts, photos, audio files, advertising identifiers, or usage analytics through the app.</p>
      <p>The app is built with iOS WKWebView and Capacitor. Observation records and assessment data are not sent to the developer's server.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">3.</span>Data Stored on the Device</h2>
      <p>During app use, the following data may be stored locally on the user's device:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Recorder display name</strong>: a name or nickname entered by the user, used to show who created records when files are exported.</li>
        <li><strong>Student or subject labels</strong>: app-generated numbers or optional aliases entered by the user.</li>
        <li><strong>Observation and assessment records</strong>: behavior records, timestamps, duration, intensity, ABC details, activities, setting events, notes, interview records, MAS responses, support plans, and app settings.</li>
        <li><strong>Local identifiers</strong>: device-local identifiers and observer identifiers generated by the app to organize records and prevent duplicates during import/export. These values are not sent to the developer and are not used for advertising tracking.</li>
        <li><strong>Subscription status cache</strong>: the app may store whether premium subscription access is active in order to provide subscription features.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data is local app data stored on the user's device for app functionality. It is not data collected by the developer.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">4.</span>Student Personal Information</h2>
      <p>The app is designed to identify students by automatically generated labels such as <code>2026 Student 1</code>. Users may optionally enter aliases or notes for convenience, but we recommend not entering directly identifying information such as real names, school names, contact details, addresses, or government identification numbers.</p>
      <p>If a user enters personal information in free-text fields, that information remains on the device by default. However, if the user exports or shares records, the information may be included in the exported file. Users should review the file contents before sharing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">5.</span>Home Widget and App Group Storage</h2>
      <p>To provide the iPhone home-screen widget, the app and widget may store limited data in an iOS App Group shared container.</p>
      <p>The shared container may include the selected student's display name or initial, target behavior name, today's and weekly counts, last record time, and pending records created from the widget. This data is used only between the app and the widget and is not sent to the developer's server.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">6.</span>Storage, Export, and Sharing</h2>
      <p>App data is stored on the user's device. The developer does not store or sync data through a developer-operated server, an external server, or a cloud database.</p>
      <p>When the user intentionally uses record export, PDF report generation, or Excel report generation features, the app may create password-protected files. These files may include student observation data, assessment content, notes, and report contents.</p>
      <p>File sharing occurs only through the user's explicit action via the iOS share sheet or an app selected by the user. After sharing, the recipient app, messenger, email service, or cloud service processes the file under its own privacy policy.</p>
      <p>Depending on the user's device settings, iCloud or iPhone backup may back up local app data. This is controlled by the user's device, Apple ID, and iCloud settings.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">7.</span>In-App Subscriptions and Payment</h2>
      <p>touchABA may use Apple App Store in-app subscriptions to provide premium features. Subscription purchases, renewals, cancellations, refunds, and payment method processing are handled by Apple and are subject to Apple's terms and privacy policy.</p>
      <p>The developer does not directly collect or store users' card numbers, bank account details, or other payment method information. The app may use Apple StoreKit to check subscription entitlement status and may store the active subscription status locally inside the app.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">8.</span>Third-Party Sharing and Sale</h2>
      <p>The developer does not sell or provide app data to third parties. The current version does not use ad networks, analytics tools, or crash reporting tools.</p>
      <p>Apple's own terms and privacy policy may apply to App Store functions such as app installation, updates, subscriptions, payments, refunds, reviews, security, and policy processing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">9.</span>Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <p>Local data remains on the device until the user deletes it. Users can delete locally stored data through the app's reset-all-data feature, by deleting the iOS app, or through device settings where available.</p>
      <p>Exported files and copies shared to other apps cannot be deleted remotely by touchABA. Users must delete those files and recipient copies themselves. Because the current app does not create user accounts, account deletion procedures do not apply.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">10.</span>Security</h2>
      <p>The app does not transmit observation data to a server. Exported files, PDF reports, and Excel reports may be protected based on a password set by the user. However, the security of local data also depends on the user's device lock, OS security, backup settings, and management of sharing recipients.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2><span class="n">11.</span>Children's Privacy</h2>
